[32m+[m[32m### Slide 2: The Problem Space[m
[32m+[m[32m* **Slide Content:**[m
[32m+[m[32m  * Fragmented study materials across PDFs, notes, and previous year questions.[m
[32m+[m[32m  * Static learning methods that fail to adapt to a student's pace.[m
[32m+[m[32m  * Lack of instant, qualitative feedback (especially for oral examinations and subjective answers).[m
[32m+[m[32m  * Overwhelming syllabus management and poor time allocation.[m
[32m+[m[32m* **Speaker Notes:**[m
[32m+[m[32m  > "Students today face a massive fragmentation of their resources. They have PDFs scattered everywhere, static notes that don't adapt to their learning style, and most importantly, they lack a unified system to test their knowledge interactively. Furthermore, preparing for oral vivas or analyzing what topics are most important from past exams is entirely a manual process."[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Slide 3: The Solution - Academic OS[m
[32m+[m[32m* **Slide Content:**[m
[32m+[m[32m  * Centralized Subject Workspaces.[m
[32m+[m[32m  * Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) for personalized context.[m
[32m+[m[32m  * Automated Syllabus Parsing & Study Planning.[m
[32m+[m[32m  * Dynamic, AI-driven assessment generation.[m
[32m+[m[32m* **Speaker Notes:**[m
[32m+[m[32m  > "Academic OS solves this by unifying everything into one clean workspace. By leveraging advanced Retrieval-Augmented Generation—or RAG for short—the AI intimately understands exactly what the student is studying. It automatically parses the syllabus, creates personalized study plans, and generates assessments based specifically on the user's uploaded materials."[m
[32m+[m
